The gold dragon stands, reared on it's hind legs and pushing forth two keen claws. In his right claw is a medium sized scepter with a large ruby on top and a small statue of a flying dragon on top of that. The smaller dragon is facing away from the party. There are two emeralds for the large dragon's eyes, and his mouth is vacuous. You sense heat coming from the higher portion of the dragon, possibly its face, however you are not sure. His hind claws are embedded into the stone floor of the chamber. His wingspan, at least 14 feet across, makes for an aura of dread. The dragon himself stands at least 10 feet tall, though he is not fully upright. In front of the dragon is Alexander's throne-like chair. This is also gold, with a plush red pillow with gold tassles resting on the seat. The chair looks rather simple, besides being made of gold. The rest of the chamber is lit by six torches, three on one wall, and three on the other. There is a regal red carpet that leads up to the chair, and a bed against the right wall. The bed is made of a deep dark oak, but still has a red satin-like comforter over it. The left wall has a large mosaic depicting a man reaching towards the sun. Behind where you stand, you feel a cold breeze from the large opened doors, from whence the dwarf came. You can slightly see inside, it is a large room with a bluish tone that resembles sunlight, perhaps from slits in the walls, you're not sure presently. There are red mats each an equal distance away from each other positioned on the floor across the entire room. There are, however, two lines made across the room where the mats seem to have been trodden upon. You can't see where these lines originated since the door is only slightly open, and the room appears to be huge. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/bfaeryfirealongthenightshore.showUserPublicProfile?gid=sovbeos>sovbeos</A></span><br> <